### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

When using `ComponentFixtureAutoDetect` in a zoneful test, a change detection cycle is triggered before inputs have the chance to be set.

In the example below, the test will pass but a first change detection cycle will be triggered on our component causing an `NG0950` error because the template tries to read the `message` required input while it is not set yet.

```ts
TestBed.configureTestingModule({
  providers: [
    {
      provide: ComponentFixtureAutoDetect,
      useValue: true
    }
  ]
});
const fixture = TestBed.createComponent(Greetings);
fixture.componentRef.setInput('message', 'Hello!');
await fixture.whenStable();
expect(fixture.nativeElement.textContent).toBe('Hello!');

@Component({
  template: `{{message()}}`
})
class Greetings {
  message = input.required<string>();
}
```

This seems to happen because:
1. when setting `ComponentFixtureAutoDetect` to `true`, `TestBed.createComponent` will immediately attach the view to the `ApplicationRef`.
2. then a tick is triggered synchronously here: https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/87e025ae7844a11f7af0173958ae1c8295dff080/packages/core/src/change_detection/scheduling/ng_zone_scheduling.ts#L48-L60
3. so change detection is triggered on our component before we get a chance to call `ComponentRef#setInput` and the signal is read in the template before it is set.

## Questions
A. should the first scheduled tick here be scheduled instead of executed synchronously?
https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/87e025ae7844a11f7af0173958ae1c8295dff080/packages/core/src/change_detection/scheduling/ng_zone_scheduling.ts#L57
B. or should the component attachment to the `ApplicationRef` be scheduled instead of done synchronously?
Cf. https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/87e025ae7844a11f7af0173958ae1c8295dff080/packages/core/testing/src/component_fixture.ts#L111
C. should the imperative `ComponentFixture#autoDetectChanges()` be preferred to `ComponentFixtureAutoDetect`? but in that case, the test will not be zoneless-ready, so what would be the most versatile alternative?

### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

https://stackblitz.com/edit/testbed-required-input-auto-detect-error-repro?file=src%2Fgreetings.spec.ts

### Please provide the exception or error you saw

```true
Error: NG0950: Input is required but no value is available yet. Find more at https://angular.dev/errors/NG0950
```


